author: COMSOL
description: A thermoacoustic engine is a device with no moving parts that can generate acoustic energy from temperature gradients within the engine. It uses the relationship between the movement of oscillating air and the temperature changes in the air compressed and expanded by the acoustic waves. The same mechanics can be used to generate a temperature gradient by acoustic energy, which is called a thermoacoustic heat pump. This model simulates a system which couples a standing-wave thermoacoustic engine to a heat pump.
